JOHANNESBURG &#8211; Two children have died and three others have been injured in a collision in Kempton Park on Saturday night. It s understood the children, a three and five-year-old, died on the scene. Paramedics say a six-month-old baby with moderate injuries was found in the bushes in her car seat. ER24 s Ineke van Huyssteen says, Another vehicle was found in a ditch but a driver sustained no injuries. ER24 transported three patients to Sunshine Hospital. The exact circumstances are not yet known to our paramedics but local authorities were on scene for further investigation. 